        <abstract> 
<p>J. D. Hooker has described Capt. King’s Tierra del Fuego plants and CD’s Galapagos plants [in <hi rend="italic">Flora Antarctica</hi>, pt 2 (1847)] which have extraordinary interest and novelty.</p> 
            <p>A malicious person has sent George Grey, Governor of New Zealand, a letter CD had written to J. L. Stokes, containing a derogatory statement likening Grey’s expedition to "a set of school boys".</p>
        </abstract>
